Lançamento do novo logo da marca Razzo e novas embalagens\nOs produtos da Razzo são conhecidos dos brasileiros há 48 anos. Fundada em 1964\, por Salvador Razzo\, em São Paulo\, a companhia iniciou suas atividades com a produção de matérias-primas utilizadas na fabricação de produtos de limpeza e higiene.  Ao longo de sua história\, a empresa diversificou suas atividades\, dedicando-se\, primeiramente\, à produção e à  comercialização de sabão em barra e\, posteriormente\, aos mercados cosmético\, farmacêutico e químico. Site: www.razzo.com.br.

Zusammenschnitt von Leifheit Werbespots der letzten fünfzig Jahre mit vielen Klassikern. 

Im Jahr 1959 gründeten Ingeborg und Günter Leifheit die Günter LEIFHEIT KG in Nassau zur Produktion von Teppichkehrern und Bodenwischern. 1972 wurde das Unternehmen von der ITT\, New York\, übernommen.

Schon als das Ehepaar Leifheit die Marke LEIFHEIT vor nunmehr einem halben Jahrhundert aufbaute\, stand ein Aspekt im Vordergrund: nicht allein die Produktidee\, sondern der Produktnutzen ist der entscheidende Aspekt für den Erfolg.

Technik\, Ergonomie und Qualität bilden bei LEIFHEIT von jeher eine ästhetische Einheit und führen zu kreativen Problemlösungen\, die das Leben erleichtern. Eben deshalb sind LEIFHEIT-Produkte seit 50 Jahren „immer eine Idee besser\ und machen das Leben zu Hause Tag für Tag ein Stück leichter\
\n
\nSeit 1984 ist LEIFHEIT eine börsennotierte Aktiengesellschaft. Das Unternehmen zählt heute mit den bekannten Marken LEIFHEIT\
\n
\nDas Unternehmen mit Hauptsitz in Nassau/Lahn beschäftigt rund 1.200 Mitarbeiter."

Mercadotecnia Emocional 
Sin lugar a dudas la Mercadotecnia Emocional ha llegado para quedarse\, la muestra está en la publicidad y propaganda premiada a lo largo del mundo que ha logrado incrementar las ventas de productos de valor agregado y triplicar las recaudaciones de fondos para organizaciones civiles. En el rol de compra nuestra mente y su racionalidad han quedado superadas por la fuerza y pasión de las emociones\, es por esto que hemos incluido en los programas de Adiestramiento y Capacitación para Comerciantes y Fuerzas de Ventas de las empresas más grandes de México la Mercadotecnia Emocional y su impacto en el Rol de Compra. El Dr. Abraham Nosnik nos dice que la Comunicación debe de ser Íntegra\, Integral e Integrada\, así son nuestros consumidores y ciudadanos por lo tanto nuestra responsabilidad es mayor.

This is part 1 of the original cartoon animations used for the G.I.Joe Marvel comic run.  I haven't found these on youtube yet and I have always wanted to give back for all that I have taken.  Here it is!  

It is because of the initial cartoon commercials for the comics which created the demand for the daily series which was good but not as good as it could had been if it was produced along the same principles as these 30 second commercials.  I fell in love with G.I.Joe with the help of these commercials.  They were brilliant and still are after 25 years!  

After waiting 25 years\, I wish the new live action movie would live up to the exciting standards set by this groundbreaking series!  Instead\, the new G.I.Joe \Rise of Cobra" seems to be rewriting things as they go along.  So much for progress.  What I have on youtube is what I feel is G.I.Joe.  I hope everyone will agree!
\n
\nYO JOE!!!!"

The Most Important Meal of the Day is a Sesame Street song from 1993 performed mainly by the Anything Muppets. A young boy (Peter Linz) is indignant about eating breakfast; he'd rather play. Out of nowhere\, a chef (Julianne Buescher) appears and is shocked by what she hears. In an upbeat gospel song\, she sings about the importance of breakfast\, with a montage of people and Muppets enjoying their meal\, including a tiger\, a horse\, Ernie\, Elmo\, Telly\, Barkley\, and Big Bird. The boy is convinced by what he hears\, and asks his mother what's for breakfast. Performers (other than those noted above) include Lisa Buckley (as the boy's mother)\, Jim Martin\, Alice Dinnean-Vernon\, Fran Brill\, Joey Mazzarino\, and David Rudman. This song was written by Tony Geiss and directed by Lisa Simon.

http://www.pbn.ro http://www.pbv2.ro http://www.porschetimisoara.ro Noul Audi Q5:
sportiv si flexibil

•SUV-ul de performanţă de la Audi ridică ştacheta 
•Tehnologii inovative pentru o conducere dinamică
•Interior spaţios cu o multitudine de funcţii inteligente


Ingolstadt  Noul Audi Q5 combină dinamismul unei berline sport cu un interior extrem de variabil si opţiuni flexibile pentru utilizarea în timpul liber şi împreună cu familia. Motoarele puternice şi eficiente\, tracţiunea integrală quattro permanentă şi mecanismul de rulare agil au fost combinate pentru crearea unui pachet tehnologic superior\, atât pentru conducerea pe teren normal\, cât şi pe teren accidentat. Funcţiile de ultimă generaţie\, precum transmisia S tronic cu şapte trepte de viteză şi dublu ambreiaj şi sistemul de control „Audi drive select\, sunt dovezi ale sloganului Audi Vorsprung durch Technik (Progres prin tehnologie). Cel mai sportiv SUV din clasa sa este dinamic\, multifuncţional si confortabil.

Dimensiunile indică faptul că acesta este un SUV de proporţii complet noi. Având o lungime de 4\,63 m (15\,19 ft) şi o lăţime de 1\,88 m (6\,17 ft)\, noul Audi Q5 are o înălţime de numai 1\,65 m (5\,41 ft)  fiind un model mai sportiv decât toţi concurenţii săi. Mai mult\, acest SUV stabileşte un alt punct de referinţă în clasa sa\, având un coeficient aerodinamic scăzut de 0\,33.

Cu eleganţa sa sportivă şi formele sculptate cu măiestrie\, designul noului Q5 se îmbină perfect cu caracterul mărcii Audi. Partea frontală este dominată de faruri expresive în ambele părţi ale grilei mari formate dintr-un singur cadru; la cerere\, acestea pot fi înlocuite cu faruri bi-xenon şi lumini diurne cu LED-uri. Privit din lateral\, roţile mari şi marginile ridicate sunt dotări extrem de remarcabile.
Interesting advertising campaign to revamp the image of LACOSTE - giving it a more trendy\, contemporary\, and cosmopolitan look... I really like how they could conveyed the lifestyle into a theme...

香港出現過唔少連鎖餐廳、酒樓或快餐店，陪伴著唔少人度過愉快時光。幾十年來，各式各樣嘅快餐店陪住香港人成長。有啲仍然風光，有啲只能回味。你腦海閃起嘅有冇哈迪斯、陽光一代同出奇老鼠？香港飲食業一直競爭激烈，好多都風光一時。選出呢十大，你哋又食過未？ Text: Wong Ki

10) 烤雞大王
喺KFC未壟斷快餐雞市場嘅80、90年代，香港出現本土專攻食雞嘅快餐店－烤雞大王，分店多數位於日資百貨公司food court。戴上膠手套手撕全隻燒雞，配埋粟米真係非常美味，令到另一同業大家樂出「燒春雞」系列打對台，可見點樣風靡一時，可惜只得一時。港產片《最佳損友》，劉華同陳百祥等人食雞食到津津有味，就係喺烤雞大王取景。

9) 農場餐廳
農家意粉前身就係農場餐廳。農場餐廳係香港90年代興起嘅連鎖餐廳，主打簡樸西餐，以抵食、真材實料見稱，高峰時全港分店近50間，只可惜老闆陳興濤喺97年金融風暴破產，全線執笠。2000年代尾東山再起，開「農家意粉」，有分店，結果蝕成千萬，今年年初最後一家都執埋。

8) 金龍船
2000年左右狂擴充餅店同酒樓，應該係為咗上市。賣嘅點心同西餅好靚，價錢當然亦有份量，又賣過廣告，主角係蕭正楠。2003年受沙士影響，生意差，最終捱唔住全線結業。

7) 東東雲吞麵
相信好多人大多透過電視廣告認識呢家粉麵連鎖店，「東東麵，非常麵」，又唱歌又急口令，宣傳包裝真係一流，八十年代時期，東東雲吞麵快餐店業務發展蓬勃，可惜食物品質參差不穩，選擇不多，00年後陸續結業。現在喺超市間中見到東東急凍雲吞同水餃。

6) Wendy's
90年代香港出現好多美式連鎖快餐，除咗Hardee's仲有Wendy's，俾香港人多個選擇。Wendy's是第三大漢堡包快餐連鎖店，80年代以「得意妹」為名登陸香港，惜三年後敗走。91年以「雲狄斯」之名再進軍香港，高峯期擁有11間分店，可惜宣傳策略始終不及麥當勞，未受小朋友歡迎，06年撤出香港。

5) 陽光一代
當年在玻璃櫥窗前看着師傅轉動手上的薄餅，是80後小學生每天放學後最愛的節目。最記得當時其中一間舖喺沙田新城市廣場，現在近GAP服裝店果個位置，門面有塊大櫥窗睇到師傅轉Pizza，成為當時小朋友一大娛樂。屬於香港公司嘅陽光一代，由開餐廳轉型其他界別求存，例如中小學飯盒，仲有「波仔飯」，越做越大。

4) 馬里奧餐廳
專攻意大利口味食品嘅香港連鎖餐廳，裡面有咩食冇咩印象，但最記得係首電視廣告歌，有個疑似著名意大利男高音盧奇亞諾·巴伐洛堤唱歌介紹餐廳嘢食，之後有個細路大叫Mamma Mia。仲有《國產凌凌漆》銅鑼灣皇室堡槍戰一幕背後嘅餐廳門面。呢間屬於大快活集團嘅餐廳，似乎不敵同業Pizza Hut，最終逃唔過易手倒閉命運。

3) 雅香園
70年代的香港人，對24小時營業的雅香園不會感到陌生。
對呢間港式快餐店有印象嘅多數都係70後。專賣中式粉麵，80年代風行一時，希望可以殺出條中式快餐血路，當時仲推出24小時營業，創了香港飲食先河，聽前輩說，餐廳不衛生，係執笠其中一個原因。
P.S. 雅香園曾賣過電視廣告，主角係Beyond黃家強
 
2) 出奇老鼠
呢家80年代風行嘅美資連鎖餐廳好多人都記得，食Pizza又有室內遊樂場，咁樣crossover法真係好獨特，亦令小朋友樂而忘返，但最終都撤資返去美國，歡樂天地取而代之。

1) 哈迪斯
美國連鎖式快餐，90年代進軍香港。80後對於哈迪斯有深厚感情，除了炸薯圈，蘑菇飯最深入民心，可惜不敵肯德基及麥當勞，最終 2006年全線結業，原因係租金同經營權嘅問題。事實止Hardee's風光時期香港、台灣、新加坡、日本等都有分店，而家縮到只可以喺美國及中東地區先食到。

Honey (Sharon Cuneta)\, is a conservative homemaker in a twenty-year marriage to Tim (John Estrada). Honey finds a pair of sexy lingerie in her husband’s possession\, a confirmation that Tim has been seeing another woman. Not wanting to lose her family of four children\, she does not confront her husband about it and instead decides to gather more facts. She enrolls in a gym to make herself physically appealing. There\, she meets the liberal and fun-loving fitness instructor\, Frances (AiAi delas Alas)\, who helps her with her problems both inside and outside the gym. Their contrasting personalities give them different perspectives on relationships and how to raise their kids. They become the best of friends. That is\, until Honey learns that Frances is Tim’s other woman. Honey finds herself torn between saving her marriage and keeping a unique friendship. She tries to steer Frances away from Tim\, but the clueless Frances does not allow this to happen. Unwittingly\, Honey uses Frances’ habits and attitudes on Tim\, and it strengthens their marriage. Their family gets happier while Frances begins to feel Tim distancing from her. When Frances learns that she is a mistress\, she breaks up with Tim. Honey is once again caught between taking care of her heartbroken friend and keeping the mistress away from her family’s life. But what if Frances learns that Honey is Tim’s legal wife? Will this signal the end of their friendship?

Never allow yourself to be a slave to finances.

An obsessive view of money can foster unhealthy responses like greed and dishonesty. This can be true whether a person has a lot or a little. When money has that kind of power in a person's life\, they become its slave.

When we view money as just a tool\, and don't allow ourselves to get emotionally attached to it\, we are in control. Remember\, it's just printed paper with no intrinsic value whatsoever. You\, on the other hand\, are extremely valuable. The more you actively share your unique value with the world\, the greater your sense of self-worth will become.

Tên sản phẩm: Máy xay ép thực phẩm đa năng Magic Bullet
- Nghiên cứu thiết kế tại Cty hàng đầu về sản phẩm gia dụng của Mỹ Homeland Housewares LLC \, lắp ráp tại Trung Quốc
- Nguồn điện: 220Vac\, 50Hz\, Công Suất: 200W
- Trọng lượng trọn bộ: 3.5Kg\, Kích thước vỏ hộp: 27 X 27 X 34 (Cm)
- Thời hạn Báo Hành 12 tháng kể từ ngày mua
Bộ sản phẩm bao gồm 21 chi tiết:máy xay đa năng
- 1 Đế động cơ
- 1 Cốc cao\, 1 Cốc thấp 
- 1 Dao thẳng\, 1 Dao chữ thập
+  4 Ca chứa\, 4 nắp đậy màu đen để tạo ca chứa thành ly. 
- 2 nắp giữ kín\, 1 nắp thoát hơi\, 1 nắp gạn lọc.
- 1 Cối xay \, và 1 bộ lọc ép nước hoa quả
- 1 Sách hướng dẫn sử dụng và công thức chế biến các loại món ăn\, thức uống
Sản phẩm được bảo hành 12  tháng
ĐẶC ĐIỂM NỔI BẬT CỦA:  Máy xay đa năng
- Sử dụng dể dàng và nhanh chóng\, thời gian thực hiện chỉ tính bằng giây
- Là dụng cụ chế biến thực phẩm vô cùng tuyệt vời cho tất cả mọi người mọi nhà\, chỉ một chiếc máy Magic Bullet là có thể thay thế cho các loại máy như xay sinh tố\, ép trài cây\, xay thịt\, xay cá\, xay cà phê\, đánh kem\, đánh trứng\, nhào bột\, xay/băm nhuyễn các loại gia vị thảo mộc\, .....
- Máy có hai lưỡi dao phù hợp chế biến tất cả các loại thực phẩm
- Kèm theo máy có sách hướng dẩn công thức pha chế các loại rượi\, cocktail\, café\, nước ép\, sinh tố và các món ăn mà chỉ tím thấy ở các nhà hàng sang trọng mới có
CÁCH SỬ DỤNG. 
- Rất đơn giản: Chỉ cần cho các nguyên liệu\, thực phẩm vào trong các phụ kiện phù hợp (Cốc\, Ca\, Bình\, Bộ ép...) cùng với lưỡi dao thích hợp và đặt lên đế động cơ rồi ấn nhẹ trong vài giây là bạn thực hiện xong món ăn bạn ưa thích.
- Máy sử dụng hộp inox\, thiết kế và kết cấu giá dao chắc chắn. Bàn cốc được phân biệt kiểu mới\, khiến cho máy sử dụng an toàn\, thuận tiện vệ sinh máy.
- Máy còn có cốc xay thịt dung lượng lớn\, vừa dùng để xay thịt\, vừa dùng để xay hoa quả rất hữu dụng.
Giữa tiết trời mùa hè nóng nực\, hấp dẫn làm sao khi cầm trên tay 1 ly hoa quả nghiền sữa chua mát lạnh. Cơ thể bạn sẽ được thanh nhiệt giải độc thật nhanh chóng. Đặc biệt hơn\, nếu bạn muốn trổ tài nấu những món ăn kiểu Tây mới lạ như spaghetti\, khoai tây nghiền sốt thịt bò...  máy xay đa năng Magic Buller sẽ là trợ thủ đắc lực của bạn.
Thay vì phải mua máy ép\, máy xay sinh tố\, máy xay thịt...\, chỉ với chiếc máy xay đa năng\, tất cả nhu cầu \xay" của gia đình đều được đáp ứng.
Máy xay đa năng được tích hợp nhiều tính năng chỉ trong một thiết bị duy nhất. Mỗi khi có nhu cầu xay loại thực phẩm nào\

This was a great job to be apart of. I turned it down 4 times\, I pushed my schedule out over 4 months and the client still waited for me. It was a job I did not really want to do because I did not think it could be done properly in Jakarta. Also working for big global companies with many voices\, and having two AD agencies at the same time on set... I really doubted that it was possible to do a good job. But mid way through pre production with PLUSH PICTURES in Jakarta\, i quickly realized that the project was turning into something grand. I had a vision\, but did not think Jakarta had the film experience to pull it off. I was gladly mistaken. All the crew and especially the art director WAIKI really bought there \A\" game to the table. Everyone could see this turning into something big... everyone started to get behind it... The client and agency were letting me do my thing and did not get in the way at all. We ended up with a great TV Commercial that everyone is proud of. My thanks goes out to all involved. Great work guys... Jakarta's film industry just stepped up to international levels.\nI shoot around the world alot\

Jake (John Malkovich) and Tina (Andie MacDowell) are a glamorous American couple camping out in a suite in a swank London hotel. They're unable to settle their account\, which when the movie begins stands at about six thousand pounds\, because Jake\, a speculator\, has blown all his money on a bad investment. Jake and Tina are unmarried and have no permanent address; they're charming\, attractive drifters\, getting by on style. In a sense\, they're throwbacks to the sophisticated and slightly disreputable couples who floated airily through thirties romantic comedies: no-strings types who stick together for the best shallow reasons-for sex and laughs and the shared kick of living the high life without having to work too hard. The picture\, written and directed by Michael Lindsay-Hogg\, is conceived as high-style fluff\, but it never delivers quite as much irresponsible fun as it promises. It's like a Lubitsch movie without the speed and the grace and the blissful inconsequentiality. Malkovich\, however\, is as unaccountably magnetic here as he was in \Dangerous Liaisons.\" His performance is a postmodern mutation of thirties style\

All 5 commercials for Mattel Electronics PlayCable Adapter for their Intellivision video game system\, featuring baseball legend Mickey Mantle.  These were first aired in 1982.  This is a unedited copy of the master tape.  A copy of these were provided to Keith Robinson of Intellivision Productions.

The PlayCable system\, introduced in 1981\, allowed local cable-TV system operators to send Intellivision games over the wire alongside the normal TV signal. Subscribers to the service could then use a special converter—the PlayCable Adapter—to download the games to play on their Intellivision game consoles.

The PlayCable Adapter connected to the Intellivision via the game-cartridge slot on the side\, just like any other game. Once connected\, switching on the Intellivision would bring up an on-screen menu showing which games were available to play. (Typically\, several different titles would be available at any given time\, with the available selection changing from month to month.) The system was not truly interactive\, though; the program code for all of the available games was simply broadcast over the cable connection constantly\, and whenever the user selected a game the Adapter would simply wait until that particular bit of code came past\, grab it off the line\, and load it into its internal memory. The Intellivision would then read the Adapter's memory as if it were a normal ROM cartridge.

Unfortunately\, the PlayCable Adapters only had 4K of RAM in them. While this was sufficient for most Intellivision game titles in 1981\, it wasn't long before more complex games started appearing on 8K and 16K cartridges\, which the PlayCable could not support. This made the system increasingly less attractive to customers\, since it was limited to supporting only the older game titles\, and the system was eventually discontinued in 1983.

Since the PlayCable adapters were rented from the local cable-TV company\, rather than purchased outright\, they all had to be returned when the system was discontinued. Thus\, very few of them are known to still exist\, making them an extremely rare item for Intellivision collectors.

For more information\, check out INTV Funhouse's website: http://www.intvfunhouse.com/hardware/playcable/

http://ow.ly/3d49A Toy Story 3 is a 2010 American 3D computer-animated film. It is the third and currently final film in the Toy Story series.[4] The film was produced by Pixar Animation Studios and released by Walt Disney Pictures. Lee Unkrich\, who edited the previous films\, and co-directed the second\, took over as director. In his place\, Ken Schretzmann is the editor. Toy Story 3 was also the first of only two films to be released theatrically with 7.1 surround sound\, the second being Step Up 3D.

Tom Hanks\, Tim Allen\, Joan Cusack\, Don Rickles\, Estelle Harris\, John Ratzenberger\, Wallace Shawn\, Jeff Pidgeon\, Jodi Benson\, R. Lee Ermey\, John Morris\, and Laurie Metcalf all reprised their voice-over roles from the previous films. Jim Varney\, who played Slinky Dog in the first two films\, and Joe Ranft\, who portrayed Wheezy and Lenny\, both died before production began on the third film. The role of Slinky was taken over by Blake Clark\, while Ranft's characters and various others were written out of the story (Wheezy\, Etch\, and Bo Peep\, for example\, are mentioned in the beginning as having been sold). New characters include voice-overs by Ned Beatty\, Timothy Dalton\, Bonnie Hunt\, Whoopi Goldberg\, Jeff Garlin\, and Michael Keaton.

Toy Story 3 was released worldwide from June through October in Disney Digital 3-D\, RealD and IMAX 3D. The feature broke the record of Shrek the Third as the biggest opening day North American gross for an animated film unadjusted for inflation and a big opening with an unadjusted gross of $110\,307\,189.[5][6] It is also the highest-grossing opening weekend for a Pixar film\, as well as the highest-grossing opening weekend for a film to have opened in the month of June.

The film is currently the highest-grossing film of 2010 in the United States and Canada\, and the highest-grossing film of 2010 worldwide. In July\, it surpassed Finding Nemo to become Pixar's highest ever grossing film at the North American box office. In early August\, the film became Pixar's highest-grossing film worldwide and surpassed Shrek 2 as the highest-grossing animated film of all-time worldwide; in late August\, Toy Story 3 became the first ever Pixar film and animated film in history to make over $1 billion worldwide. It is currently the 5th highest-grossing film worldwide of all time

This video is the history\, usage\, and contexts to which the slang term 'herb' may be used. A little video that myself and a few other herbs put together.
The word 'Herb' was once thought to be the shortened version of the male name Herbert. Well back in the 1980's Burger King started an advertising campaign around that name\, but during the early to mid 1990's this name adapted itself into slang.

I have been saying it since I was a nino\, due in part to my brother Nick who introduced me to the term in the mid 1990's.

All you herbs out there\, you don't know who you are\, but we do.

The third commercial break in Predator 2 starts with a bit of U-rated soft-focus pornography featuring Andy Williams (not participating in the pornography\, fortunately) and advertising the Peugeot 306.

Next is an advert for a failure on the part of Camelot\, the kind of thing that lost them the licence a couple of years later (they got it back when the Government remembered how good they were at stuffing envelopes full of banknotes). TV Dreams was intended to be interactive - not only could you win the chance to appear on the TV show fronted by Anthea Turner the following month\, but you could also buy a scratchcard and play along at home! Except it was so half-arsed no-one bothered. And the show didn't work\, mainly because the winning audience members couldn't actually do anything because it would violate the concept of a lottery. And the TV play game was hosted by a CGI animated-on-the-fly barfly woman with the voice of Kate Robbins\, superimposed on the live footage of the draw\, which was a terrible idea\, and demonstrated such by promptly disintegrating into a bunch of lines\, leaving Kate to desperately improvise her way out of it live on TV. And Camelot ended up getting rapped on the knuckles for encouraging gambling. So yeah\, well done.

Then\, incomprehensible then-Newcastle manager Kenny Dalglish explains why the Bristol and West is so bloody great. There were a lot of these\, all with the same basic script and the same pre-Channel 4 whipping-round-to-reveal-the-logo ending. John Peel was on another one. He only advertised things he actually used\, so presumably he had an account at the B&W and ate Trios.

Next is Jif\, which apparently consists of several little men who run around your kitchen kicking germs to death. And whistling.

Apparently it's late at night by now\, because here's one of those faintly nightmarish adverts for a singles network chatline thing that I had trouble believing anyone ever used. These things were never even close to specific as to what they consisted of\, but then they didn't really need to be.

If that was faintly nightmarish\, the next one is an actual nightmare\, a condensed version of one set in some kind of netherworld that apparently exists in the mind of a Care Bear with a fever. The voice of Joe Pasquale completely fails to explain what's going on. Precisely what this is doing being advertised in the middle of Predator 2 is anyone's guess.

Then that Lynx Apollo thing is back\, and there's a reprise of that terrible Lottery idea\, and then a glimpse at the late Kevin Peter Hall.

Engreído y seguro de sí mismo\, cabezota y bien parecido\, Max Skinner es un exitoso financiero especializado en comercio de bonos. Tiburón financiero a orillas del Támesis\, Max devora a sus competidores en un intento de hacerse con el mercado europeo. Su última conquista ha dado como rédito un beneficio neto de siete cifras\, con gran pesadumbre para sus rivales vestidos primorosamente en Saville Row. El triunfo de Max está en perfecta consonancia con su filosofía: ganar no lo es todo\, ¡es lo único que hay!

Muy poco después\, Max recibe una carta desde Francia que contiene malas noticias: su viejo tío Henry ha fallecido. Max\, el pariente más cercano de Henry\, es el único beneficiario de su herencia: una finca que incluye una casa de campo en Provenza y un viñedo\, La Siroque\, en la que Henry ha estado cultivando vides durante más de treinta años.

Max viaja hasta la casa de campo en la que pasó las vacaciones de los veranos de su infancia con su excéntrico tío\, a quien no ha visto o escrito en años. Mientas Max atiende a los asuntos legales de su herencia\, se encuentra suspendido de empleo y sueldo por su firma\, pendiente de una investigación por una más que cuestionable transacción de bonos.

Con su futuro en Londres en el aire\, Max a regañadientes empieza a habitar en la casa de campo. Se reúne con el veterano cuidador de las viñas de la finca\, Francis Duflot (que todavía se encarga de las vides después de tres décadas)\, a quien Max recuerda de sus visitas infantiles. La exuberante mujer de Duflot\, Ludivine\, la casera de la finca\, recibe a Max de forma muy cálida.

Max no tiene muy claro si sabrá hacerse a la vida en el sur de Francia ni si sentirá cómodo allí. Llama a su mejor amigo\, el agente inmobiliario de Londres Charlie Willis\, para preguntarle qué papel puede desempeñar hacer un pequeño viñedo y una finca como La Siroque en el mercado actual. Charlie le advierte a Max que las pequeñas bodegas con un buen producto pueden generar varios millones de dólares\, pues el vino de boutique\, elaborado en pequeñas cantidades\, es lo más en las tiendas de vino. Es dinero en el banco para Max si al final pierde su trabajo.

Mientras Max recupera con cariño los recuerdos de sus veranos pasados (junto a un hombre cuya sabiduría y filosofía ayudaron a Max a dirigir su exitosa carrera)\, aun contemplando un oscuro futuro\, surge un contratiempo con la repentina llegada de una decidida chica veinteañera de California llamada Christie Roberts. Christie\, natural del Valle de Napa\, alega ser la hija ilegítima de su fallecido tío. La revelación\, de ser cierta\, le convierte en prima de Max y\, de acuerdo con la ley francesa\, en la beneficiaria de La Siroque.

Sospechando que Christie quizás sea una impostora\, Max indaga en su pasado haciéndole mil y una preguntas\, mientras anda a la greña con ella por el destino de la bodega\, cuyo vino está a la altura del peor vinagre que se pudiera imaginar. Max\, que ha probado el terrible vin de pays (vino de mesa) de La Siroque\, también encuentra algunas botellas en la bodega del tío Henry con el nombre de Le Coin Perdu ('El Rincón Perdido'). Este misterioso y legendario vino de garaje se ha vendido a miles de dólares en el mercado negro durante años\, según Fanny Chanel\, la atractiva propietaria de un café local por la que Max se ha sentido atraído.

¿De dónde sale ese vino y por qué insiste tanto Duflot en seguir en La Siroque sea cual sea el destino del viñedo? Y\, ¿qué decir de algunas vides muy poco comunes descubiertas en la finca por Christie\, que el brusco vinatero argumenta que son un experimento y un afamado enólogo ha estimado de escaso valor?

Los recuerdos de Max y el transcurso del tiempo sacan a relucir emociones y sentimientos que pensaba ya perdidos\, y le permiten tener en nueva estima la filosofía de vida de su fallecido tío Henry y de la vida en la Provenza: \No hay ningún otro lugar en el mundo en el que uno pueda estar atareado haciendo tan poca cosa ¡y disfrutándolo tanto!"

Saindo do eixo Rio-São Paulo\, faço agora uma homenagem aos nosso compadres mineiros. Esta é uma compliação de videos retirados das contas MemoriaPUCTV\, BrazilWorldTV e Comte e eis aqui a mais completa coletânea de vinhetas da saudosa TV Itacolomi de Belo Horizonte\, a primeira emissora de TV fora do eixo Rio-São Paulo\, que entrou no ar em 8 de novembro de 1955 pelos Diários Associados de Assis Chateaubriandt\, pertencentes à TV Tupi. Essa emissora permaneceu no ar por quase 25 anos\, sua imagem alcançava cerca de 600 municípios mineiros e por muito tempo era líder imbatível de audiência em Minas Gerais\, atingindo altos picos de 80%\, cujos índices dificilmente (ou raramente) foram igualados na capital mineira. Contando com 300 funcionários\, sua programação era composta de peças teatrais\, humor\, teledramaturgia\, jornalismo\, programas de auditório e esporte\, além de ter sido pioneira nos chamados telecursos matinais. O curioso é que por 10 anos seguidos\, sua programação era inteiramente ao vivo e foi somente a partir de 1965 que chegou o primeiro aparelho de video-tape na emissora\, quando sua grade foi reformulada com a aquisição de modernos equipamentos para a época. A liderança absoluta de audiência foi sempre ressaltada em suas vinhetas e ostentou tal posição por 17 anos até ser \driblada\" pela Rede Globo nos boletins do IBOPE\

女優の井川遥さんが10月8日、東京都内で行われた出演するCMのイベントに登場。8日から東京と大阪で期間限定でオープンする店「角ハイボール CMのあのお店」のオープニングイベントで井川さんは、落ち着いた白のシャツにエプロン姿で登場し、角ハイボールで乾杯するシーンもあった。「この雰囲気も手伝って、炭酸が強いからスカッとしますね。やっぱりおいしいです」とコメントし、オープンした店については「ものすごい完成度で、まさに“あのお店”そのものだなと」と感想を語った。

同店は井川さんが出演しているサントリーのテレビCMの舞台となっている店を再現したもので、13日までの期間限定で六本木ヒルズ「大屋根プラザ」と、グランフロント大阪「ナレッジプラザ」の2カ所でオープンする。お店では角ハイボールやからあげなどのフードを販売する。

井川さんは実際に知人などにリクエストされて「（ハイボールを）作ったこともあります」とにっこり。「混ぜすぎないことで香り高く、炭酸の強い発泡した感じが楽しめます」と家庭で作るコツも披露した。

Transcript:
• Consumers have different lifestyles\, which means the things they buy (and why they buy them) are different. So why do they all see the same TV ads?
• TV advertising used to be pretty straightforward. A single media buy could give you access to a huge part of the population. Unfortunately\, things aren't that simple anymore.
• More channels\, more devices\, more fragmentation -- today's audiences are a lot harder to pin down.
• No surprise then that many marketers are turning to online advertising. Online\, it's relatively easy to target specific audiences\, tailor ads to make them more relevant and to measure their performance. But when it comes to reach and popularity\, television still reigns supreme.
• Wouldn't it be great if you could combine the efficient reach of TV with the effectiveness of highly targeted ads? Well\, now you can -- with Visible World's targeted TV advertising.
• Our targeted TV advertising makes the most of the broad\, efficient reach of television by enabling you to target different ads to different consumer groups\, based on more meaningful criteria than just age and gender. It's all about making your messages more relevant - and effective.
• Complicated? Not with Visible World's award winning technology. We've automated the process of targeting TV ads to make it easy\, fast and smart. Up-to-date reporting lets you measure what's going on\, so you can fine tune your efforts\, even in the middle of the campaign.
• The result? Everyone's happy. Viewers see ads that are relevant to them. And marketers see their ads work harder\, with less effort. And that makes TV ads more valuable for everyone.
• Find out what targeted TV advertising can do for you.

In the age of digital video recorders (DVRs) many advertisers have lamented that consumers aren't as influenced by ads because they have the ability to fast forward through or even skip the commercials.

But new research from Duke University's Fuqua School of Business suggests the opposite could be true: Consumers might be more influenced when they aren't focusing on advertisements and their defenses are down.
 
The researchers also found that while watching fast-forwarded ads\, consumers are most influenced when they see brands they perceive as very different from each other in a back-to-back ad block.
 
\We feel these findings have important implications for the way advertisers place their promotional messages -- both in traditional television spots\

In 1989 the UK was gripped by Yo-Yo Fever and everywhere you looked\, there they were. You couldn't open a newspaper or switch on a television with seeing Yo-Yos. Everyone knew about       Yo-Yos\, they were those plastic discs on a string that went up and down\, right? Wrong! Since the days of the depression in the USA\, when the Yo-Yo craze swept America and kids all over the country entered contests and won bicycles and footballs\, the Yo-Yo had been transformed into a precision instrument that can perform literally hundreds of tricks\, both easy and very complicated. 

Here in the UK\, the Yo-Yo craze was part of a Coca-Cola advertising campaign\, which had been run for over 40 years in just about every country worldwide\, some several times. As a result of the Yo-Yo craze in the UK\, Coca-Cola\, at the time part of Cadbury/Schweppes\, increased their sales and literally put their brand in the hands of their target Youth Market. Over 4 million Coca-Cola trademarked Yo-Yos were sold in a 10 week campaign.

Yo-Yo contests were held all over the UK and the final contest held at Alton Towers\, presented by the late Jeremy Beadle. Here is the story of the 1989 Yo-Yo campaign in the UK.

Het IKEA Sofa Experiment:
Kleine veranderingen. Groots effect.

Wil jij ook wel eens iets veranderen in de inrichting van je huis maar weet je niet waar beginnen? En zou ook jij het liefst willen dat deze aanpassingen vooral makkelijk zijn en weinig kosten? Wel\, dan ben je niet alleen!

Daarom stelt IKEA je nu het Sofa Experiment voor. Hierbij laten we je het verhaal zien van 5 uiteenlopende families in België\, die allemaal een probleem hadden met hun sofa. Maar dit om verschillende redenen: lelijk\, versleten\, niet gezellig\, té klein of onhandig. 
Door simpelweg hun sofa te vervangen en enkele textielaccessoires toe te voegen zoals een tapijt\, gordijnen\, kussens of plaids\, verkregen we een groots effect. En niet alleen in hun interieur\, ook op hun humeur. 

Ontdek hun verhaal en laat je inspireren om ook jouw woonkamer deze herfst warm aan te kleden.

　ファッション誌「Seventeen」などで活躍するモデルで女優の中条あやみさんが、大塚製薬のイオン飲料「ポカリスエット」の新CMキャラクターに起用されたことが4月16日、明らかになった。中条さんは新CM「Jump」編でセーラー服姿で街中を疾走しており、「約500人のエキストラのみなさんと呼吸を合わせて全力疾走したときは、走る距離も長くてすごく大変でしたが、終わったときは達成感があり、とても楽しかったです」と笑顔で振り返った。18日から全国で放送。

　中条さんは「ミスセブンティーン 2011」でグランプリを受賞し芸能界デビュー。2011年9月から雑誌「Seventeen」（集英社）専属モデルとして活躍しており、12年にはドラマ「黒の女教師」（TBS系）で女優デビュー。昨年9月にはホラー映画「劇場版 零～ゼロ～」で映画初出演で初主演に抜てきされ注目を集めた18歳だ。

　「自分は、きっと想像以上だ。潜在能力をひき出せ。」をメッセージにした新CMは、高校の全校朝礼のシーンから始まる。中条さん演じる女子高生はつまらなそうに時間を過ごしていたが、校長が突然、ロックバンド「クイーン」の名曲「WE WILL ROCK YOU」を歌い出すと、一転、何かに駆り立てられるかのように学校から駆け出し、眠っていた潜在能力が花開く……というストーリー仕立ての内容になっている。

　CMは、学校や街の中、高層ビルの屋上、港などさまざまな場所で撮影された。どの場所のロケでも「走った」という中条さんは「想像以上にたくさん走ったので筋力も鍛えられました」と振り返っていた。なお、撮影に臨む中条さんに迫ったメーキングドキュメンタリー動画も公開する。

　昨年、AT限定小型二輪免許を取得した大島が、商品の楽しさを伝える「部長」として、菅田が「新入部員1号」として登場。大島が通りすがりの菅田に愛車を自慢し、前2輪が滑らかに傾く様子を「リーン！」と体を可愛らしく傾けながら表現する。これを見た菅田も思わず「リーン」と口ずさんでしまう内容。

Carlitos el dulcero\, Rap dominicano 2015
http://indashop.tk
-Hey muchacho\, dulcero!!! 
-Dígame señor 
-Cuál es tu nombre? 

Mi nombre es Carlitos y vendo dulce\, 
para sobrevivir aunque mi vida no ha sido del nada dulce ha sido muy amarga 
y el destino me cobra a la corta lo que a los otros quizás a la larga\, 
soy muy joven aunque la verdad 
he sentido la vejez del sufrimiento a mi corta edad pero usted entenderá 
que la vida es dura y se suda cuando la cruda realidad grita NECESIDAD. 
Sería bueno trabajar para progresar\, mejorar y cambiar de mi status social 
pero lo que gano es para alimentar a mi familia que en casa siempre me han de esperar con él. Estomago partido\, las tripas haciendo ruido 
porque esta es la hora que todavía no han comido 
esta es la hora que solo he vendido 2 dulces y tengo hambre 
¿A dónde se fue mi suerte? A donde? 
Si las gentes supieran con el cariño que lo hago 
para ganarme unos míseros centavos 
para sustentar esta vida inerte y evadir la fragancia rancia que me acosa con la muerte. 
Hay gentes que me ignoran\, por mis aramos me catalogan 
como delincuente o que consumo droga 
no saben la razón de esta vida recia 
solo se fijan en mi sudor y esta cara sucia\, 
muchos se burlan otros intentan humillarme 
pero no entienden que yo quisiera superarme 
que yo no elegí esta cadena para condenarme 
y la sociedad me ve como un problema debo resignarme. 
A ser marginado a caminar y no ser notado 
por el pasillo de los olvidados solo estoy vivo por 2 motivos 
por los cuales respiro por los cuales los dulces van conmigo. 

-Woww que penosa tu situación\, no está estudiando? 
Se ve que eres un muchacho trabajador y con deseo de superarse y tus padres no te dan ayudas? 

Bueno\, cuando yo tenía 10 años mi padre nos abandono\, 
no se imagina cuanto nos dolió 
mi hermano pequeño no lo recuerda 
porque el tenia 2 años apenas cuando papi nos dejo\, 
mi madre sufrió tanto que cayó en cama\, 
tuve que soltar los estudios y coger la limpia bota para emprender el camino 
y dejar los juguetes para convertirme en el juguete del destino\, 
yo mantengo a mi madre y a mi hermano 
con los dulces la vida me gano aunque pierdo la mía pero no hay un día 
en que las lagrimas no visiten la puerta de mis ojos por eso esta rojo algunos días. 
No he fácil la vida que llevo pero mi conciencia es limpia\, 
aunque yo este sucio como un pordiosero 
no me atrevo a atracar\, a robar ni matar prefiero sudar y honradamente trabajar yo quiero. 
Mi madre me ayudaba hace un tiempo pero se sentía cansada y en casa tuvo que quedarse 
y todo se complico cuando el doctor la reviso y le diagnostico un incurable cáncer\, 
hay medicina que no puedo comprar\, hay tratamiento que no puedo pagar 
son caros en exceso pero algo que no tiene precio 
son los abrazos de mi madre\, su sonrisa y sus tiernos besos. 
Como quisiera que mi situación sea diferente 
un buen trabajo para que no me discrimine las gentes 
pero no entiende algo ilógico como la suciesa se refleja en la limpieza del político. 
Tome no pague lo que cuesta 
es que quiero regalarle un dulce por escucha lo que a mí me afecta 
pero yo solo quería que sepa 
que mi realidad no se palpar desde el asiento de su jeepeta.

The Volkswagen Santana is a three-box sedan\, based on the second-generation Volkswagen Passat (B2). It was first introduced in 1981 and is scheduled to remain in production (in China) until 2012.

In North America\, it was also known as the Volkswagen Quantum. In Mexico\, it was named the Volkswagen Corsar\, while in Argentina it was sold as the Volkswagen Carat. In Brazil and other South American countries it was known as the Santana\, while the Passat Variant B2 wagon was marketed as the Volkswagen Quantum. In Europe\, the Santana name was dropped in 1985 (with the exception of Spain\, where the Santana nameplate was retained) and the car was sold as a Passat. European production ended in 1988.

Wings Hauser battles monotone line delivery and Satanic cults in Mind\, Body & Soul\, a 1992 thriller by Rick Sloane (writer/director of the intentionally cheese-tastic Hobgoblins and the Vice Academy series).  We might have to track down a copy of this movie just to get the full effect of all these performances\, but for now we'll consider this a best-worst-of reel.

John Stockton had already been playing for the Utah Jazz for eight years at this point\, so it makes perfect sense that Hauser's character was named John Stockton for no apparent reason.

Also notice\, there is no intro to the second half of the show\, they go right from the bumper into another cartoon...  that doesn't occur in any of the other recordings of BBRR that I have.

Born in Warsaw\, Poland\, she grew up under the cloud of a repressive
Socialist regime.When she was five\, she lost her father when he was struck
by lightning while working as a lifeguard. That same year she was selected
to begin training for the Polish gymnastics team. For the next ten years\,
her life revolved around the state run program culminating in her being
selected for the National team for the Olympics. The best all-round gymnast
in Poland and favored to medal in the uneven bars\, a devastating knee
injury ended her dream of Olympic glory.
During her lengthy recovery\, the petite gymnast began to grow\, reaching
her present 5'9\ in record time. No longer able to put stress on her knee\

Arroz Doce Energia

A apresentadora Ana Maria Braga mostra uma receita que\, além de dar água na boca\, é super fácil de ser preparada. Trata-se do Arroz doce feito com o Achocolatado em Pó Energia Zaeli\, enriquecido com nove vitaminas e maior teor de cacau. Confira:

INGREDIENTES

• 2 xícaras de chá de ARROZ AGULHINHA ZAELI
• 1 xícara de chá de açúcar
• 1 litro de leite
• 2 litros de água
• 395 ml de creme de leite (1 lata) 
• 50 gramas de COCO RALADO ZAELI
• 1 xícara de chá de ACHOCOLATADO EM PÓ ENERGIA - ZAELI

MODO DE PREPARO

- Lave o arroz e coloque em uma panela com a água. Leve ao fogo até que fique macio e quase seco.
- Acrescente o leite\, o açúcar\, o achocolatado em pó e o coco ralado (reservando um pouco para polvilhar)
- Mantenha cozinhando em fogo brando por mais 20 minutos.
- Junte o creme de leite\, deixe mais cinco minutos em fogo brando e desligue.
- Retire do fogo e coloque numa travessa para esfriar.
- Polvilhe o restante do coco ralado e leve ao refrigerador\, sirva gelado.

亨利是個懷才不遇的編劇，日復一日過著放蕩不羈的生活，即便枕邊美女一換再換，他依然難忘舊情人凱薩琳娜。某天，亨利意外接到一個大案子，要將一本全球賣座的暢銷小說改編成劇本，而即將與他共同執筆的原著作者，竟然就是舊情人凱薩琳娜！亨利興奮不已，想趁此良機重新追回生命中的最愛；此時卻半路殺出了一名八歲女孩瑪德蓮娜，還自稱是他的女兒。為照顧這初來乍到的女兒，半本爸爸經也不懂的亨利，竟異想天開端出昔日把妹專用的拿手菜「紅酒燉香雞」來招待她，濃濃酒味卻讓八歲的瑪德蓮娜難以下嚥，只好偷偷開伙、還搞到火燒廚房。但最糟糕的是，亨利與凱薩琳娜好不容易復燃的愛情，似乎也將毀在這位天外飛來的小女孩手中。

El nuevo Cinema 3D con Smart TV revoluciona una vez más el concepto de Teatro en Casa. LG Electronics se enorgullece en presentar las nuevas innovaciones que podrás encontrar en su Smart TV.

Un modelo elegante sin bordes\, de acabado hermético y slim\, el Cinema 3D es un televisor HD con tecnología Smart\, la cual te permite aprovechar al máximo un mundo de entretenimiento online. 

Point-Draw-Move: 
Utiliza el control remoto Magic Motion para navegar\, dibujar y mover objetos en la pantalla de manera intuitiva.

Smart Share: 
Comparte tus fotos\, videos y demás contenido en tus dispositivos móviles y llevalos a la pantalla del Cinema 3D con facilidad.

Time Machine II:
No te pierdas ni un minuto de la acción con Smart TV\, que te permite pausar y rebobinar eventos en vivo... ¡graba tus partidos de fútbol!

Voice:
El nuevo Magic Motion te permite darle comandos a tu TV con tu voz. ¡Pruébalo!

LG Cloud:
Ya no te preocupes por falta de espacio en disco para tu contenido multimedia; el LG Cloud es el espacio que necesitas para almacenar tus videos y fotos que quieras conservar. 

Universal Control: 
El Magic Motion remote puede ser habilitado para que controle todos los dispositivos de tu teatro en casa.

Skype/Skype Camera:
SmartTV no solo cuenta con funcionalidad Skype integrada\, sino también una webcam HD que sale elegantemente de la parte superior del televisor para poder hacer video llamadas con facilidad.

　お笑いコンビ「ダウンタウン」の松本人志さんが、リクルートの求人情報メディア「タウンワーク」のCMキャラクターに起用されたことが7月24日、分かった。松本さんが清掃員に扮（ふん）した新CM「エレベーター」編は27日から放送されるほか、次回作で松本さんと共演できる“激レアバイト”も募集する。

　新CM「エレベーター」編は、とある雑居ビルが舞台で、夏休みのバイトを相談しながらエレベーターに乗り込む男子大学生2人に、エメラルドグリーンのつなぎ姿で清掃をしていた松本さんが圧倒的な目力とともに「バイトするなら、タウンワーク！」と訴える……という内容。松本さんの登場により緊張感に包まれるエレベーター内の様子や、力強いコメントのあとに放つ松本さんのシュールな“つぶやき”などが見どころになっており、特設サイトでは24日からCM映像を先行配信する。

　“激レアバイト”は、定期的に貴重なバイト体験を提供する「タウンワーク」のキャンペーンで、今回はエキストラとして松本さんとCMで共演でき、アルバイト当日はCM制作の美術チームとともに撮影で使用する小道具の作成にも携わることができる。バイト時期は12月上旬、場所は関東圏を予定。応募は「タウンワーク」の公式サイト内から行い、27日から8月16日まで受け付ける。

　俳優の小栗旬さんが桃太郎を演じているペプシのテレビCM「桃太郎」シリーズの第4弾が7月11日から放送される。桃太郎一行がついに鬼ケ島に上陸し、黒鬼と戦う姿が描かれている。

　同CMシリーズは、2014年3月から放送を開始。第1弾「Episode．ZERO」編で、桃太郎が犬、猿、キジを仲間にして鬼ケ島に旅立ち、続く「Episode．1」編では、桃太郎が一人で鬼に挑み敗れた過去、「Episode．2」編では、仲間である「犬」の生い立ちから桃太郎と出会うまでが描かれた。

　新しい第4弾「Episode．3」編は、キジに焦点が当てられる。キジと双子の兄「カラス」は、鳥の王国の戦士として誕生し、キジは「愛」で民を守り、カラスは「力」で一族を支配していた。ある日、さらなる「力」への欲望に負けたカラスは、強大な力を求めて鬼の仲間となり、自らも鬼と化してしまう。そして、鬼ケ島に上陸した桃太郎一行と対峙（たいじ）する……というストーリー。30秒と60秒のバージョンがある。

　小栗さんは、同シリーズについて「日本ではできないようなことだったり、普段の撮影スタイルとは違うようなことをいつも経験させてもらえます。周りのみんなから、うらやましがられる作品になっているので、そういうこともひっくるめて、すごく刺激的な現場だと思います」とコメント。新CMについては「とうとう鬼ケ島に到着して鬼との戦いが始まるので、かなりいろいろなことが変化してる。生まれ変わった新生・桃太郎が見せられるんじゃないかと思っています」とアピールしている。

　BS・CSでは、4分バージョンが13日から放送される予定で、キジとカラスの細かいエピソードとともに、キジの複雑な心理描写や奪われた兄の心を取り戻すために戦いの決意をもって鬼ケ島へ向かう姿が描かれている。9日から公式サイトで先行公開される。

　女優の木村文乃さんが、酒風味でアルコール度数0．00%の炭酸飲料「フォレスティ　森のソーダ＜レモン＆ライム＞」（サントリースピリッツ）のイメージキャラクターに起用され、新CMに出演することが9日、明らかになった。木村さんは、新CM「森の香り篇」で、「森の香りがする～」「ふぉれ ふぉれ ふぉれ フォレスティ～」といった不思議な歌を気持ちよさそうに口ずさんでいる。

　新CMは「恋人と2人きりで過ごす森の中」という設定で撮影され、リラックスした木村さんが歌を口ずさみ、「森が香るノンアルコールソーダ、フォレスティ。サントリーから」というナレーションで締めくくられる。

　木村さんは、撮影前に歌の自主練習をし、「リラックスという部分は意識しましたが、落ち着いた後にちょっと楽しくなるような雰囲気をスタッフの皆さんが作ってくださったので、私も楽しく歌うことができたと思います」とにっこり。自身の普段のリラックス方法について「何も考えずにボーッとすることでしょうか。日々の仕事の中でいろんなことを考えてしまうから、他の時間はなるべく考えないようにしています」と明かしていた。

　「フォレスティ　森のソーダ＜レモン＆ライム＞」は、甘さ控えめで、レモンとライムの味わいと、ジンを思わせる風味に、森に漂う香り成分を加えたノンアルコールソーダ。9日から全国で発売される。

Many will remember that Superfriends not only offered great DC action but also health and safety tips as well as Magic Tricks.  Here Superman discusses the dangers of taking pills out of the medicine cabinet.  Also the promo for next weeks Superfriends episode

The All-American Girls' Professional Baseball League was founded in 1943\, when most of the men of baseball-playing age were far away in Europe and Asia fighting World War II. The league flourished until after World War II\, when\, with the men's return\, the league was consigned to oblivion. Director Penny Marshall and screenwriters Lowell Ganz and Babaloo Mandel re-create the wartime era when women's baseball looked to stand a good chance of sweeping the country. The story begins as a candy-bar tycoon enlists agents to scour the country to find women who could play ball. In the backwoods of Oregon\, two sisters -- Dottie (Geena Davis) and Kit (Lori Petty) -- are discovered. Dottie can hit and catch\, while Kit can throw a mean fastball. The girls come to Chicago to try out for the team with other prospects that include their soon-to-be-teammates Mae Mordabito (Madonna)\, Doris Murphy (Rosie O'Donnell)\, and Marla Hooch (Megan Cavanagh). The team's owner\, Walter Harvey (Gary Marshall) needs someone to coach his team and he picks one-time home-run champion Jimmy Dugan (Tom Hanks)\, who is now a broken-down alcoholic. After a few weeks of training\, as Dugan sobers up\, the team begins to show some promise. By the end of the season\, the team has improved to the point where they are competing in the World Series (which is no big deal\, since there are only four teams in the league). - Paul Brenner

Obama offered a robust defense of newly revealed surveillance programs on Friday as more classified secrets spilled into public\, complicating a summit meeting with China's new president focused partly on human rights and cybersecurity.


Mr. Obama departed from his script at a health care event in California to try to reassure Americans that he had not abused government authority by collecting telephone call logs and foreigners' e-mail messages. But the disclosure hours later of secret contingency planning to target other countries for possible cyberattacks made his get-together with President Xi Jinping later in the day all the more awkward because cyberattacks by the Chinese are high on the American agenda.

The latest of three documents published over three days by the British newspaper The Guardian added to the understanding of the Obama administration's approach to national security in an age of multifaceted threats and became another factor in the renewed debate over the balance between privacy and security.

The identity of the person who gave those documents to The Guardian and The Washington Post is not known\, but The Post has described its source as a career intelligence officer angry at \what he believes to be a gross intrusion on privacy" by the Obama administration.

You know a commercial is old when it's about the dentist. Not about a toothpaste or floss\, just the concept of dental hygiene provided by a tooth care professional. It's amazing dentists ever got popular with ads like these. I mean really\, what was the point of showing this kid assaulting a foul mouthed woman walking her dog twice? 

In the second commercial we see another classic toilet paper commercial from before the Baby Face Killa's reign of terrors was uncovered. This may have been before he even started murdering\, who can really be sure of that? This does give a nice insight into his psyche though. The events in this ad may have been one of the contributing factors to his descent into madness. People just took bites of his toilet paper and then begged him to take a swing at them knowing he legally couldn't. That ain't right.

After that\, a commercial that faced the issue of alcoholic firefighters. Not something we hear about much these days\, but apparently it was sort of a big deal a few decades ago. Apparently\, a pet store in New York caught fire and one of the firefighters thought the lady who worked in there was an orangutan because the flames had burnt her hair and made it an orangey hue. This obviously raised a lot of questions about the value of life and whether or not the firefighter should have put his full effort into saving what he perceived to be a primate as if it were a human (which it was). This was back when coffee commercials tried to get political. Thank god that didn't last.

影片中，小男孩Sam有个形影不离的好朋友，一隻可爱的企鹅Monty，他们一起生活、一起出游，甚至还看了电影，直到圣诞节时，Sam送了Monty一份礼物，是另一隻可以与牠作伴的企鹅！牠们见面时甚至还开心的玩在一起。然而，等Sam的妈妈走进房间，一切才真相大白，原来Sam拿在手中的是两隻娃娃，分别是Monty与新的企鹅娃娃，这也暗示着原来Monty只是Sam幻想中的好朋友。
根据《镜报》的报导，原来这段名叫「企鹅Monty」（Monty the Penguin）的影片，是英国百货公司John Lewis的圣诞广告。心理医师Sheila Keegan表示：「这则广告中有很多小小的感动，也许第一时间裡你不会注意到它们，但它们却合力带给你一个大家都想要却不常实现的完美圣诞节。」
网友在看过影片后也纷纷发表意见，很多人觉得这真是太可爱了，有人说自己从来没有因为广告而哭的，不过也有人半开玩笑的表示，现在的小孩其实比较喜欢iPad当作礼物。

The Coca-Cola Arctic Home is the world's first temperature-controlled installation created to raise awareness of the polar bear's disappearing habitat. Inside the display is a sculpture of two polar bears\, surrounded by real water. By pledging to reduce their carbon footprint or spreading awareness of the cause via video\, text or Twitter\, individuals could decrease the temperature inside the Arctic Home\, keeping the polar bear's habitat frozen\, while building awareness of the effects of global warming. The habitat traveled across Canada in February and March 2013 as a part of Coca-Cola's global Arctic Home initiative in partnership with WWF-Canada.

Situated in a private courtyard in the heart of Shoreditch\, First Option is a versatile 2000 sq ft converted Victorian zip and suspender factory that has served as a highly acclaimed hire location for over thirty years. The studio is designed specifically for film\, TV and stills\, but is also a great event space. First Option comprises a 1000 sq ft split level space adjoining a 500 sq ft bespoke kitchen together with a smaller 230 sq ft prep kitchen. Within the main studio space - accessible via a spiral staircase - is an additional 204 sq ft mezzanine with 30 ft of built in desks and work tops\, ideal as a production office or as a storage/ holding area.

Both the studio space and the main kitchen have high pitched roofs\, with exposed Scotts pine roof trusses and sanded wooden floors. Our fabulous main kitchen has marble and wooden work tops\, along with many features designed specifically for shooting purposes; including a mobile island with built in hob\, and a glass lighting balcony – great for lighting the kitchen from outside and therefore minimising the need for lighting cranes. The studio is ideal for shooting daylight and has an abundance of natural light from both the north and the south\, but also can achieve almost full blackout.

It's been 15 years since the Playstation 2 hit the market and we still have fond memories of that second Sony console. Over the years of the PS2 Sony has made some of the weirdest commercials ever made... have a look!

1. Bambi – https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=T4tOvkvCvwQ 
For some reason David Lynch made a PS2 commercial in which a deer demolishes a truck. Why? Because the Playstation 2 is a different place\, with different rules. 

2. Delivery guy – https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4zU6uwcEWa8 
A delivery guy\, who turns out to be a chick\, comes to some guys Motel room to bring a PS2 and play some games. The lyrics of the song in the background are amazing by the way... 

3. Lost for words – https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=msMehuZo3x8 / https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=h28Kbdfmvbk 
Another commercial shot by David Lynch. We don't even have a clue what we are looking at here... How the hell is this an actual commercial? 

4. Get on board – https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jk354q3oPlc
We don't even get to see the console or any games in this commercial. But hearing the song “Get on board” and seeing people fighting to reach the top of a human mountain\, is a beautiful way of explain the struggle to reach the top of the leaderboards... isn't it? 

5. Epic game commercial – https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=25pGBIQI46c
This Japanese Playstation 2 commercial is pretty cool. Sony introduces some of the game characters which will be featured in PS2 games. Can you imagine a modern version\, with modern game characters? That would be freaking epic! 

6. Missing piece – https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iFnDAGO2Wa4
Sony used a commercial about an eskimo talking about a missing piece of a jigsaw puzzle. Stating you don't need eye sight\, but you do need vision. Yup\, we guess drugs were easily accessible around the Sony offices back in those days. 

7. Fleas – https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Uvb5myzohN8

For some reason a video about the fictive conditioned life of a flea actually is a Playstation 2 commercial. Sure\, what they mean is that you can escape your regular life with a PS2\, but this is way too philosophical in our opinion. 

8. Playstation 9 – https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UZejZiZX9_M 
Let's make a commercial about the future of Playstation. We paint a picture of a Playstation 9 and in the end we will give you it's predecessor\, Playstation 2. What a way to kill the hype... 

9.  African safari – https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gA1jOD-MBxE 
Young girls and sports mascottes? Stockbrokers and a pit crew? After watching this for 30 seconds we still have no idea what they are talking about. Fun anyone? Yes please.

Do you have fond memories of the PS2 era? Let us know in the comments below!

Thought it was terrible and never showed it to anyone.  One day about 4 years later\, I happened to be dubbing it in Engineering and the promotion manager saw it and wondered why I never showed it to him.  He said he would have aired it or at least used it somewhere.  Oh\, well.....

A couple of years ago\, I found that someone had uploaded a bad-quality copy to you-tube.  I really wonder where it came from.  I had the only copy of it in existance.  When I left KCRA in 1992\, I thought I took the only copy with me.

Cuando estudiaba en la secundaria y trabajaba en un local de pizzas en Jeffersonville\, Indiana\, el fundador de Papa John's\, John Schnatter\, sintió que a las cadenas nacionales de pizza les faltaba algo: una pizza tradicional\, de calidad superior entregada en la puerta del cliente. Su sueño era algún día abrir un restaurante que llenara ese vacío.

En 1983\, John se llevó su título en administración de la Ball State University y regresó a Jeffersonville\, Indiana. Allí\, a los 22 años\, tiró abajo un armario de artículos de limpieza que estaba en la taberna de su padre (Mick's Lounge)\, compró equipo usado de cocina por un valor de $1600\, y comenzó a vender pizzas en el fondo del bar.

Desde el primer día John supo que podía hacer una mejor pizza usando masa fresca e ingredientes de calidad superior\, y se negó a abandonar ese compromiso con la calidad. Funcionó\, y a la gente le encantó su pizza. En 1984\, John abrió su primer restaurante Papa John's\, y Papa John's se ha ido fortaleciendo desde entonces. Actualmente\, Papa John's es el reconocido líder de la categoría de la pizza y ahora tiene más de 3\,500 restaurantes propios o franquiciados en 50 estados y 29 países. Más de 25 años más tarde\, hay algo que sigue igual\, Papa John's aún cumple con el eslogan de la marca: \Mejores Ingredientes. Mejor Pizza."

"Hacer una pizza de calidad usando mejores ingredientes ha sido la base de Papa John's por más de 25 años. Me comprometo a que Papa John's no se desvíe de la base de calidad y superioridad sobre la cual se construyó la empresa. Siempre nos esforzaremos por ser su 'Mejor' empresa de pizza"."

Aussie Pete at just 17 years of age\, 80s hairstyle and all. This TV commercial for Breaka flavoured milk\, was the most expensive ad ever produced at the time in Australia and was more like a huge budget mini film. In terms of $$ per second\, it cost more to make than a full-feature film.

The commercial\, the first for the then new beverage and the begninning of a long-running campaign (It's a Dream of a Drink')\, ran for 5-years across all TV stations in prime time and in cinemas along with all new releases... it got so that I could not walk the streets of Brisbane without being recognized as 'the Breaka Boy'.

The pretty models sourced for the ad\, were Australia's best and most well-known\, and some people old enough to remember might recognize one as the drummer from the popular 1980s all-girl band\, Sheeba (hope I spelled it correctly).

The video here is a conversion from the original VHS video to digital (thanks to my brother\, Michael) of the one minute version of the commercial\, along with a current affairs story (Brisbane's State Affair) covering the 'behind the scenes' and interviews with producers and directors.

Finally\, if you stay watching long enough\, somehow a small snippet from my DJ days (no sound) at Manhattan nightclub - the largest and most popular venue at the time - regularly at least 2000 to 3000 patrons on any night of the week - owned and run by my then bosses and good friends\, Gerry Bellino and Vic Conte\, who were portrayed in the fourth series of 'Underbelly'. (It was the 'in' place in it's day).

Not surprisingly\, I was known in my DJ days of the 1980s\, as 'Breaka'... a nickname long since forgotten.

The attached is a very rare 'blast from the past' - enjoy!!

BREAKA - IT'S A DREAM OF A DRINK....

Toucan Sam was a lover\, a father\, and a commercial star. It seemed he was at the top of the world\, until his addiction to Froot Loops began to interfere with his work\, and even his family. None of this was helped when his wife\, Toucan Samantha\, was shot by robbers in 1992. His sons tried everything\, but Sam was descending into a downward spiral of depression out of which none could revive him. This is the lost tape of a 1993 interview\, just weeks before his tragic death\, that details the events of the last few months of his life.

From 1995\, a few promos from Disney Channel\, one of those networks that changed so much that constant comparison is made between its old and new incarnations..  The BEAUTIFUL ident/lineup dates to 1991 I think\, and was used to introduce the night time lineup.  It's always been one of my all-time favorite branding pieces.

I hate to be the one to throw cold water on nostalgia\, but old-school Disney Channel was frankly never that great.  I mean\, look at this junction - Disney World infomercials\, history documentaries\, teacher awards\, country specials.  Kids programming wasn't that great either - old\, forgotten imports\, old Disney afternoon series\, you get the idea.  Oh\, yeah... and this was a premium channel that you had to pay to see.

If I had to pick between this and the current\, teen girl focused Disney\, I'd pick the latter.  Because\, unlike here\, there's at least programming somebody would watch.

http://602communications.com. Everyone loves cheering for the little guy. In this three-minute emotional marketing lesson video\, emotional marketing expert Graeme Newell shows how some of the world's best advertisers tap our love of the underdog\, then attach that feeling of transcendence to everyday products.

What is customer focus? It's how the best advertising campaigns use core emotional drivers to connect with their customers on a significant\, meaningful level -- and Football provides a perfect place to do all that and more. As Graeme Newell points out in this short marketing video\, Football fans love the game for a lot of reasons\, most of which have nothing to do with the sport itself. The idea of a scrappy\, tough kid working harder than everyone else and achieving fame and glory lies at the core of the experience.
Positioning a brand to fit that same attitude is the essence of what we do here at 602 Communications. We hone in on the best advertising campaigns and best television ads to find out what your customers love. Football doesn't take a lot of special gear.  It's a sport where even the poorest kids can triumph. Mediocre advertisers will seize upon the glory and fury of Football\, but the best advertising campaigns will show the self-made man who clawed his way to the top by sheer force of will. With this focus acquired\, we can start to cultivate a real relationship with the customer.
What is customer relationship marketing? It's how customer-focused brands show that they share the same values and passions as their customers. Football fans are passionate about the Cinderella story -- rags-to-riches paved with blood\, sweat and tears. Customer relationship marketing is honing in on that feeling. Deep in our hearts\, most of us believe we're an undiscovered star\, and that we work harder and longer than most people.  Maybe we too can get the big promotion\, find love\, or achieve greatness. The best television ads are the ones that leave the customer thinking: \Yea\

Has that rusted\, torn-up\, beater of a car that you drove all through high school and college finally collapsed? Are you in the market for a new car but don't really know where to start? With the help of Federal Auto Loan\, you have a chance to get approved for a quality car loan fast through one of our lender or dealer partners!

A car loan is a substantial financial commitment; and it is a commitment that is often handled poorly by first-time car loan buyers. Don't get caught up in making the mistakes of others! A general rule to keep in mind is this: If you cannot squeeze your auto loan into 48 months\, do not purchase the vehicle! If you do\, you are headed down a path of destruction. In addition\, it is also a good idea to put 20% down. It is a common statistical fact that many first-time car loan buyer who break one (or both) of these two rules runs into trouble with their vehicle at a later time. It is never a good idea to be in the position of owing more on your loan than your car is worth.

Having little to no credit history creates hassle for many first-time buyers trying to get approved for an auto loan. However\, this is where Federal Auto Loan can help! Assuming you meet some general criteria\, such as a steady income of $1600 a month or more and an established pattern of paying your bills on time\, Federal Auto Loan can probably help get you approved for your first car loan\, with our online process\, in no time at all!

Whether you are in need of a new or used car for your first-time auto loan\, FederalAutoLoan.com is here to assist you! By submitting a simple online auto loan application\, Federal Auto Loan will submit your information through a secure connection to one of our lender or dealer partners\, who will do their best to help you get financing. 

Financing your first car does not have to be a scary or tedious process. With the help of Federal Auto Loan you can save both time and maybe money as well on your auto loan. By using FederalAutoLoan.com\, the tedious work of trying to find a dealer or lender to help you is done in advance! So what are you waiting for? This is a Knight Rider inspired commercial for OPET - the biggest Turkish fuel oil distribution company in Turkey.
The main charakters are Cem Yilmaz as Mike and a talking car - G.I.T.T. You can easily recognize Michael Knight & KITT in them. :)
This is the first commercial\, the begining. :)

Translation:
Boss: Mechanic Mike...
GITT: Mechanic Mike is out\, who's asking?
Servant: Who's talking?!
GITT: I'm GITT\, 'Güzel İnsan Taşıma Taşıtı' (Nice Person Carrying Vehicle).
Boss: Nice.
Servant: The car was talking?
Cem Yılmaz: Hello there.
Woman: Mr. Cem congratulations.
Man: Here\, your crystal apple award.
Cem Yılmaz: Hold on what's the rush\, we just started the ad. Let's cover this up so this isn't classified as an under cover (subliminal) advertisement\, right GITT?
Servant: What did it say?
Boss: Whooowhoo.
Boss: If you're ready\, lets go. Mike?
Cem Yılmaz: Let me slip into something more comfortable. Don't touch the car.

Boss: Our people are very uneducated and unaware of things when it comes to fuel consumption Mike. Traffic\, the environment\, you have a lot of work to do on these subjects.
Cem Yılmaz: Worry not! We will inform everyone! Right GITT?
Cem Yılmaz: It's me\, it's me... alarm.
Boss: Anyway\, this is your licence.
Cem Yılmaz: Nice.
Boss: These are your cards.
Cem Yılmaz: OPET cards. I will use these in future adventures.
GITT: Ooh\, we're getting gas from OPET bro?
Cem Yılmaz: Sure thing son\, OPET\, your favorite. He goes nuts when he hears OPET.
Boss: Umm\, before you leave I want to introduce you to someone.
Cem Yılmaz: Hopefully not someone unneccessary?
Boss: Our head technician\, Banu!
Banu: Hello.
-Button on dash reads 'wedding'\, and the car 'dresses up' as a typical wedding vehicle in Turkey.
Cem Yılmaz: I hope you don't mind\, he got a little excited and went into wedding mode.
Banu: Is that the case? I designed a watch for you. This watch will allow you to communicate with GITT.
Cem Yılmaz: Oh Really\, doll (hands Banu the doll). Lets see if it works. What time is it GITT?
GITT: You got a watch on your hand bro.
Cem Yılmaz: Good\, it works. Keep the doll. Ok then\, may all of this be prosperous and benificial.

Narrator: A man. A car. A fuel giant.

The Compact Valiant and Lancers  A Bodies weren't so lucky and tended to rust as did the B bodies of 1962. 歌手の和田アキ子さんが3月20日、人気アニメ「進撃の巨人」を題材としたスマートフォン向けゲームアプリ「進撃の巨人 -自由への咆哮-」（DeNA）の新CMに起用されることになり、東京都内で行われた発表会に登場した。以前からアニメの劇中に登場する巨人に「似ている」と言われていた和田さんだが「まさかCM出演の話がくるとは思わなかった」とオファー時の感想を語った。

「進撃の巨人」では初のスマートフォン向けゲームアプリで、巨人の侵入を防ぐため人類が築いた壁の外へと追放された者同士の生存をかけた戦いを描くバトルゲーム。新CM「現実の巨人　登場」編は、とある焼肉屋を舞台に「壁の上から超大型巨人が顔をのぞかせる......」という名シーンを再現したもので、和田さんは\現実の巨人"として出演しており、お笑いコンビ「カラテカ」の入江慎也さんと矢部太郎さんも登場する。

オファーをもらってから作品を見直したといい、「巨人が人間を食べるシーンとかあって、最初は"どうなのかな"と思ったけれど、とても面白かったし、引き込まれた」と語り、「『現実の巨人』って言葉って面白い。気に入りました。これから電話でも使っていこうかな『もしもし、現実の巨人です』って」とまんざらでもなさそうな表情。入江さんと矢部さんが巨人に対して恐怖するシーンについては「ふだんから私に対してビビッているので、あれは"素"」とからかった。

「現実の巨人　登場」編は21日から全国で放送。また和田さんは「現実の巨人　走る」編にも出演し、28日から放送される。"

The next commercial break from the Christmas Day matinee of Mary Poppins starts with an ad for the newly minted Disneyland Paris\, in which an adorable small girl with adorable diastema tries to guess the age of her grandfather\, Field-Marshal Douglas Haig. The magic of Disney makes him younger I guess. Hopefully they left before he reverted into a foetus.

Next\, SURFING GNARLY FROSTIES SURFING SURFING. Another showing for this inappropriately timed breakfast cereal advert with breakers big as condos. Why this is going out on Christmas day is beyond me. Maybe Tony is Jewish.

Then\, Lunn Poly again! Whereas the previous one\, featuring Father Christmas back-talking to his reindeer\, had a fairly short shelf-life for obvious reasons\, this one with the snowmen would generally last the entire winter\, unto March or so. The lipless puppets make for easier redubbing\, too. Note the xylophone adaptation of Walking in the Air on the soundtrack.

Now\, I'm sure you were getting worried that there weren't any sales this time around. Don't worry\, here's some Raymond Briggsian animation and a song by the Commodores - rerecorded by session artists\, naturally - to draw your attention to the January sales at Debenhams. I don't like department stores. They're too big. I drown.

Then\, the DFS hivemind returns and Commander Vorshak gets another chance to assert his alpha-male status \Don't-" "DON'T MISS IT AT DFS". You half expect him to piss on her leg for good measure.

http://www.facebook.com/superbullen.film.de Nun\, zwölf Jahre später\, kehren Tommie (Tom Gerhardt) und Mario (Hilmi Sözer) wieder auf die große Kinoleinwand zurück. Die zwei Underdogs aus Köln-Kalk\, sind die dümmsten Polizisten Deutschlands und stehen kurz vor ihrer Entlassung. (Auch die Frage drängt: Wie kommen zwei derartige Loser überhaupt zur Polizei?) Doch da naht ihr bislang größter Fall: Der Geißbock „Hennes\, geliebtes Kult-Maskottchen des 1. FC Köln\, ist entführt worden! Der Verein\, die Spieler und natürlich die Fans sind am Boden zerstört. Ohne den Talisman können die Profis den Pokalsieg vergessen. Tommie und Mario\, beide glühende FC-Fans\, sehen endlich ihre Chance\, sich als echte Superbullen zu beweisen und für alle Zeiten unkündbar zu machen Eine hochchaotische Jagd quer durch Deutschland beginnt. Und schon bald glauben die beiden zu wissen\, wo sich der Geißbock befindet: Er kann nur in München sein\, nirgends anders als beim FC Bayern\, dem Gegner im Pokalfinale ... es kommt zum dramatischen Showdown in der Allianz-Arena\, wo Tommie und Mario allerdings selbst die größten Böcke schießen...

Jaarlijks eten we gemiddeld 45 kilogram suiker. Dat is heel wat. Ook getest op mensen toog naar de gemeentelijke bassischool Sint-Brixius-Rode in Meise. Waarom eten kinderen zo graag suiker? En waarom eten ze er zo veel van? Twee dagen lang hebben we 40 kinderen van het vierde leerjaar op de proef gesteld.\nDe eerste dag kreeg de helft van de kinderen traditionele\, minder zoete ontbijtgranen aangeboden en de andere helft gezoete ontbijtgranen. Wat bleek? De kinderen die gezoete ontbijtgranen kregen\, aten maar liefst 30% meer dan de kinderen die traditionele ontbijtgranen kregen. Zoet doet dus eten!

Take a behind the scenes look at how Alzheimer's Society made our TV commercial and hear from the people who created it.

For the first time ever\, Alzheimer’s Society is running an advertising campaign to make people more aware of the Society and how we can support people affected by dementia.

Our research shows us that many people still believe that dementia is a normal part of getting old and the main symptom is loss of memory. However\, the TV ad featuring a typical family sitting down to a Sunday lunch\, shows how isolating it can be for someone with dementia\, even as part of a warm and loving family.

Interested in getting the latest updates from the Society?
Follow us on Twitter -- http://www.twitter.com/alzheimerssoc
Like us on Facebook - https://www.facebook.com/alzheimerssocietyuk
___

Who are we?

Alzheimer's Society is the leading support and research charity for people with dementia\, their families and carers.
 
What is dementia?

The term 'dementia' is used to describe the symptoms that occur when the brain is affected by specific diseases and conditions. Symptoms of dementia include loss of memory\, confusion and problems with speech and understanding.

Support the fight against dementia and visit us at
http://www.alzheimers.org.uk 

If you have concerns about Alzheimer's disease or about any other form of dementia\, please contact the Alzheimer's Society National Dementia Helpline on 0300 222 1122.

There are no computer graphics or digital tricks in these images.

Everything that you see happened in real time exactly as you see it. 
The recording required 606 takes and in the first 605 takes there always was something\, usually of minor importance\, that didn't work.
It was necessary for the recording team to install the set-up time after time and it took several months to achieve.

This commercial (at the time) turned out to be the most displayed in the history of the Internet.

There are only six Honda Accords built by hand in the whole world\, and to the horror of Honda engineers\, the recording team disassembled two of them for the recording.
Everything you see in the sequence (besides the walls\, floor\, ramp and still mostly assembled Honda Accord) is part of those two automobiles.
The voice is that of Garrison Keiller.

The commercial was so well received by Honda execs when they saw it\, that their first comment was how amazing the computer graphics were. They almost fell out of their chairs when told that the recording was real without any graphics manipulation.

By the way\, about the wind shield wipers in the new Honda Accords\, they were sensitive to water and designed to start working as soon as they get wet. The tires were weighted heavily on the right side\, which is how they 'roll uphill'.

When their new guardians forbid 16-year old Andi (Roberts) and her younger brother\, Bruce (Austin) to have a pet\, Andi has to use her quick wit to help find a new home for their dog\, Friday. The resourceful kids stumble upon an abandoned hotel and using Bruces talents as a mechanical genius\, transform it into a magical dog-paradise for Friday - and eventually for all Fridays friends. When barking dogs make the neighbors suspicious\, Andi and Bruce use every invention they have to avoid anyone discovering who let the dogs in.

เรื่องย่อ 
เรื่องราวมันส์ๆ ขำๆ ซึ้งๆ ของสามยอดชายแห่งแก๊ง3G เพื่อนซี้ผู้รักการลัลล้าเป็นชีวิตจิตใจ แม้ภรรยาจะโหดแค่ไหน ก็ยังพลิ้วไหวหนีไปมีกิ๊กได้ตลอด แทน(ชาคริต) จุ้น(เกลือ) ตู๋ (เจี๊ยบ เชิญยิ้ม) ในวีรกรรมสุดแสบซ่าส์กับการหลบหลีกศรีภรรยาสุดโหด! ด้วยฝีมือกะล่อนขั้นเทพ แต่มีรึที่แก๊งภรรยาจะยอมง่ายๆ และแล้วมาตรการขอคืนพื้นที่หัวใจก็เกิดขึ้น เมื่อโบว์ (ส้ม ธรรมรส ) น้อยหน่า(หนูเล็ก ก่อนบ่าย) เจ๊จุ๋ม(ฮันนี่ ภัสสร) ตามจับผิดติดตามพฤติกรรมทุกฝีก้าวชนิดGPSยังเรียกแม่ สามีตัวดียังแอบไปจี๋จ๋าสปาร์ครัก ซูซี่(นก อุษณีย์) นางแบบสุดฮ๊อต โดยหารู้ไม่ว่ากำลังกระตุกหนวดเสือเจ้าพ่ออย่างจัง และสุดท้ายเหมือนว่าสถานการณ์จะดีขึ้นเรื่อยๆ แต่ทว่า...คนมันเคยเจ้าชู้ จะหยุดลัลล้าได้จริงเร้อ...

Aershan\, a bottled water brand\, is famous for its natural mineral water. As the company gets water from nature\, they know water scarcity and the importance of water-saving quite well. The client wanted to establish an environmental-friendly image and increase brand awareness.

The unique insight which shaped the idea was that people in large groups when drinking bottled water easily throw half empty bottles away because they forget which bottle is theirs. On the bottle label\, we paint a layer of coating that can be easily scratched off. People can just use their finger to mark their bottle however they want\, like with their name\, a sign or an even artistic picture. Now each water bottle becomes unique and easy to distinguish.

The brand has successfully created an environmentally friendly impression. The campaign also added another element described as “art on the bottle”\, winning more favor of consumers and raising brand awareness. Client’s Weibo (Chinese twitter) followers have increased 38% after the launching of the new bottle. The campaign has made more than 230\,000 impressions within one month\, helping boost sales increase.

Hey Guys\, I have not been myself lately so that's why no new videos for awhile.  I want nothing more than to get back into the swing of things and start making new videos.  I miss you guys very much.  Any words of encouragment would be awesome.  Anyways\, here is a TV Commercial I did back in September 2011.  As soon as I got back from the island we had filmed this\, I went into my Diabetic Shock thingy.  It was weird like something from flying or whatever had pushed my body over the edge and finally the signs of diabetes kicked in.  I am feeling alot better now days.  It's all a mental game now that I am starting to win.  The family is doing awesome and they all miss you as well.  I will be making videos again soon...maybe even today.  I just want to share this with you guys and hope it brings a smile to your face.  God Bless all of you who support me and make me feel special everyday.  Please Rate\, Comment and Subscribe to me and my family!
